    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-11-15T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-11-15T06:00:00-05:00" n="113"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d113">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72119/2635: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-11-15T12:00:00+01:00"
                            >November 15, 1918—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received November 16—12:15
                        a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2356. My 2347 [<hi rend="italic">2346?</hi>].<note n="3" xml:id="d113fn3">
                        <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>.</note> In conversation with Swiss Minister, he
                    said that he has had no instructions from his Government on the subject but
                    Switzerland, he believes, would be willing to take in the small part of the
                    Tyrol known as Vorarlberg, if the population there were substantially unanimous
                    in desiring it, but would not be willing to go beyond this. To take in Tyrol
                    would change completely the character of Switzerland.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Nelson Page</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
